task.description:
Create tests/integration/orchestration/test_acquisition_flow_smoke.py with:
class TestAcquisitionFlowSmoke: - test_acquisition_flow_importable() — imports run_acquisition_flow without error - test_acquisition_flow_has_prefect_decorator() — AST check: @flow decorator present - test_acquisition_flow_returns_dataclass() — result has .n_volumes, .data_dir, .dvc_version fields - test_acquisition_flow_skips_if_data_ready(tmp_path) — if imagesTr/ already has 70 files, skip download - test_acquisition_flow_produces_dvc_tag() — DVC tag format "minivess/v{n}" returned - test_acquisition_flow_manual_fallback_message() — if download fails, returns instructions dict
class TestAcquisitionFlowConfig: - test_hydra_config_has_acquisition_experiment() — configs/experiment/acquisition.yaml exists - test_data_dir_from_env() — flow reads DATA_DIR from os.environ (Rule #22)

Create src/minivess/orchestration/flows/acquisition_flow.py:

@dataclass
class AcquisitionFlowResult:
    data_dir: Path
    n_volumes: int
    dvc_version: str | None
    manual_download_required: bool
    instructions: str | None  # populated if download fails

@task(name="check-dataset-ready")
def check_dataset_task(data_dir: Path) -> bool:
    from minivess.data.downloader import is_dataset_ready
    return is_dataset_ready(data_dir)

@task(name="download-minivess")
def download_minivess_task(data_dir: Path) -> int:
    from minivess.data.downloader import download_minivess
    return download_minivess(data_dir)

@task(name="dvc-tag-dataset")
def dvc_tag_task(data_dir: Path, version: str) -> str:
    from minivess.data.versioning import create_data_version_tag
    return create_data_version_tag("minivess", version)

@flow(name="minivess-acquisition")
def run_acquisition_flow(
    data_dir: Path | None = None,
    force_download: bool = False,
) -> AcquisitionFlowResult:
    _require_docker_context()
    data_dir = Path(os.environ.get("DATA_DIR", "/data")) / "raw" / "minivess"
    ...

Move download logic from scripts/download_minivess.py into
src/minivess/data/downloader.py (importable module).
scripts/download_minivess.py becomes a thin CLI wrapper calling downloader.py.

Add OME-TIFF → NIfTI conversion for real microscope data (non-EBRAINS input). Uses tifffile + nibabel (both already in pyproject.toml or add via uv add). Library-First: tifffile for reading, nibabel for writing.
@task(name="convert-ometiff-to-nifti") def convert_ometiff_task( input_dir: Path, output_dir: Path, voxel_size_um: tuple[float, float, float] = (1.0, 1.0, 1.0), ) -> list[Path]: Reads *.tiff / *.tif / *.ome.tiff in input_dir. Writes NIfTI to output_dir/imagesTr/. Returns list of output paths.
Flow uses this task when input_dir contains TIFF files (not NIfTI). Skipped for EBRAINS/ZIP input (already NIfTI).
